Curry & Sriracha Roasted Chickpeas

2 c cooked garbanzo beans or 1 can (15oz) drained, rinsed, and patted dry
1 heaping tsp sesame, coconut, or olive oil
1 heaping tsp sriracha
1 heaping tsp curry pwder
dash or two garlic pwder
mineral salt, to taste

Preheat oven to 400F. Place ingredients in a medium size bowl and combine will to coat. Place in a single layer on a roasting pan or baking sheet. Bake ofr ~40-45 min, mixing them around every 15 min or so until they have a nice roasted look and are crispy. Keep a close eye on them in the last 10-15 min as some may burn. Let cool 10 min before serving.

Notes:
play around with spices; alternative options: chili powder, cayenne, cumin, thyme, smoked paprika, vinegar & salt, cinnamon, lime, garam masala, salt & cracked pepper, lemon pepper, nutritional yeast, etc.
